name: tsinfer

new_version_errors.0.2.2:
The recipe did not change in the version migration, a URL did not hash, or there is jinja2 syntax the bot cannot handle!

Please check the URLs in your recipe with version '0.2.2' to make sure they exist!

We also found the following errors:

 - could not hash URL template 'https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/tsinfer-{{ version }}.tar.gz'

raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "tsinfer" %}
{% set version = "0.3.0" %}
{% set sha256 = "a39200c91885270a2890c1771823d293e75f22ec96c008918f8a196df6488a7e" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/tsinfer-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  number: 1
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps -vv
  entry_points:
    - tsinfer=tsinfer.__main__:main
  skip: true  # [py<37]

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
  host:
    - numpy
    - pip
    - python
    - setuptools-scm
  run:
    - attrs >=19.2.0
    - daiquiri
    - humanize
    - python-lmdb
    - numcodecs >=0.6
    - python
    - six
    - sortedcontainers
    - tqdm
    - tskit >=0.3.3
    - zarr >=2.2,!=2.11.0,!=2.11.1,!=2.11.2
    - {{ pin_compatible('numpy') }}

test:
  imports:
    - tsinfer
  commands:
    - tsinfer --help

about:
  home: https://github.com/tskit-dev/tsinfer
  summary: Infer tree sequences
  description: |
    tsinfer infers succinct tree sequences from observed genetic variation data
  license: GPL-3.0-or-later
  license_family: GPL
  license_file: LICENSE
  doc_url: https://tskit.dev/tsinfer/docs
  dev_url: https://github.com/tskit-dev/tsinfer

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - benjeffery
    - jeromekelleher
